.SH NAME
ViewTimeline \- ViewTimeline
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]ViewTimeline\f[B]\f[R] interface of the Web Animations
API represents a view progress timeline (see CSS scroll\-driven
animations for more details).
.PP
Pass a \f[CR]ViewTimeline\f[R] instance to the \f[CR]Animation()\f[R]
constructor or the \f[CR]animate()\f[R] method to specify it as the
timeline that will control the progress of the animation.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.TP
\f[B]ViewTimeline()\f[R]
Creates a new \f[CR]ViewTimeline\f[R] object instance.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
\f[I]This interface also inherits the properties of its parent,
\f[CI]ScrollTimeline\f[I].\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]subject\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns a reference to the subject element whose visibility within its
nearest ancestor scrollable element (scroller) is driving the progress
of the timeline and therefore the animation.
.TP
\f[B]startOffset\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns a \f[CR]CSSNumericValue\f[R] representing the starting (0%
progress) scroll position of the timeline as an offset from the start of
the overflowing section of content in the scroller.
.TP
\f[B]endOffset\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns a \f[CR]CSSNumericValue\f[R] representing the ending (100%
progress) scroll position of the timeline as an offset from the start of
the overflowing section of content in the scroller.
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
\f[I]This interface inherits the methods of its parent,
\f[CI]ScrollTimeline\f[I].\f[R]
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Displaying the subject and offsets of a view progress timeline
In this example, we animate an element with a \f[CR]class\f[R] of
